proper motions, where MSPs have velocities\nrelative to circular motion of 77 +/- 6 km/s, as determined as part of our\nGalactic MSP population model. We find that, due to the natal kicks, there is\nan approximately 10% increase in each of the bulge MSP spatial distribution\ndimensions and also the bulge MSP distribution becomes less boxy but is still\nfar from being spherical.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Sep 2021 10:02:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-20"}
